Localization:

Create ".ts" file:

pyside6-lupdate main.py .\src\ .\src\backend\ImageSaver.py .\src\backend\MessageBoxFactory.py .\src\backend\WarningDialogGenerator.py -ts .\localization\translations\main_gui_ru.ts

Open Qt Linguist tool and do translations there:

pyside6-linguist

Convert .ts files to .qm files using lrelease tool:

pyside6-lrelease .\localization\translations\main_gui_ru.ts -qm .\localization\translates\main_gui_ru.qm
pyside6-lrelease .\localization\translations\main_gui_ru.ts -qm .\src\resources\translations\main_gui_ru.qm

Don't forget to do 'Resources' next